RUN: ! test -s %t.stdout
RUN: echo 'nvptx-as: unsupported '\''.target sm_'\'' directive in preamble' >> %t.stderr.golden
RUN: cmp %t.stderr.golden %t.stderr


Special handling re CUDA 11.0, "Support for Kepler 'sm_30' and 'sm_32' architecture based products is dropped", and CUDA 12.0, "Kepler architecture support is removed" (that is, sm_35, sm_37).

Preamble '.target sm_3': doesn't exist; still special-cased to '--gpu-name sm_%target_as_arch0'.

RUN: rm -f %t*
RUN: sed -e 's|sm_30|sm_3|g' < %S/../bare-1.s > %t.bare-1.s
RUN: %target_as_dummy_ptxas_cmd -v -o /dev/null %t.bare-1.s > %t.stdout 2> %t.stderr
RUN: cmp dummy_ptxas_log.golden %t.dummy_ptxas_log
RUN: ! test -s %t.stdout
RUN: sed -e 's|sm_30|sm_3|g' < verbose_stderr-sm_30.golden > %t.stderr.golden
RUN: cmp %t.stderr.golden %t.stderr

Preamble '.target sm_30': special-cased to '--gpu-name sm_%target_as_arch0'.

RUN: rm -f %t*
RUN: %target_as_dummy_ptxas_cmd -v -o /dev/null %S/../bare-1.s > %t.stdout 2> %t.stderr
RUN: cmp dummy_ptxas_log.golden %t.dummy_ptxas_log
RUN: ! test -s %t.stdout
RUN: cmp verbose_stderr-sm_30.golden %t.stderr

Preamble '.target sm_30x': doesn't exist; diagnosed.

RUN: rm -f %t*
RUN: sed -e 's|sm_30|sm_30x|g' < %S/../bare-1.s > %t.bare-1.s
RUN: %target_as_dummy_ptxas_cmd -v -o /dev/null %t.bare-1.s > %t.stdout 2> %t.stderr; r=$?; [ x"$r" = x1 ]
RUN: ! test -f %t.dummy_ptxas_log
RUN: ! test -s %t.stdout
RUN: echo 'nvptx-as: unsupported '\''.target sm_30x'\'' directive in preamble' >> %t.stderr.golden
RUN: cmp %t.stderr.golden %t.stderr

